What landed (one file: lance-graph-contract/src/codegen_spine.rs)

  Additive:
    pub trait RouteBucketTyped {
        type Kind: Copy + Eq;
        fn kind(&self) -> Self::Kind;
        fn id(&self) -> &str;
        fn id_owned(&self) -> String { self.id().to_string() }
    }

    // Back-compat bridge: every existing RouteBucket becomes
    // a RouteBucketTyped<Kind = OdooMethodKind> automatically.
    impl<T: RouteBucket> RouteBucketTyped for T {
        type Kind = OdooMethodKind;
        // ... delegates to RouteBucket
    }

  Four new tests in the existing mod tests block:
    - route_bucket_typed_accepts_non_odoo_kind
        (OpBucket impls only RouteBucketTyped with its own OpKindFixture enum)
    - route_bucket_typed_generic_consumer_accepts_op_kind
        (generic fn over RouteBucketTyped<Kind = OpKindFixture> compiles + dispatches)
    - route_bucket_blanket_impl_preserves_odoo_consumers
        (legacy OdooBucketCompat usable as &dyn RouteBucketTyped<Kind = OdooMethodKind>)
    - route_bucket_typed_generic_consumer_accepts_odoo_via_blanket
        (proves the blanket bridge actually bridges, not just compiles)

  Two UFCS disambiguations in pre-existing tests:
    - inside the same #[cfg(test)] mod tests block, `use super::*` brings
      BOTH traits in scope, so bare `bucket.kind()` is ambiguous. Replaced
      with `RouteBucket::kind(&bucket)` in 2 call sites. Semantics unchanged.
    - downstream consumers are NOT affected: they import RouteBucket only,
      RouteBucketTyped is not pulled in by `use lance_graph_contract::*`.

